    "**2.** Two qubits are initialized in the quantum state $|\\psi\\rangle = \\frac{1}{\\sqrt{3}}(|00\\rangle + |10\\rangle - |11\\rangle)$. Write the state as to a column vector. Use SymPy quantum. \n", 
    "\n", 
    "*Handwritten part:* Is the state entangled? Why or why not? Is the state of the first (leftmost) qubit well-defined as a ket? If so, what is the state of the qubit? What is the probability of measuring the first (left) qubit to be in the state $|1\\rangle$? Suppose you measure the first (left) qubit and find it in the state $|1\\rangle$; what is the state of the system now (remember about the normalisation)? " 
   ]

    { 
     "name": "stdout", 
     "output_type": "stream", 
     "text": [ 
      "State as a column vector:\n", 
      "Matrix([[sqrt(3)/3], [0], [sqrt(3)/3], [-sqrt(3)/3]])\n", 
      "\n", 
      "Probability of the first qubit being in state |1⟩:\n", 
      "0.666666666666667\n", 
      "\n", 
      "State of the system after measuring the first qubit in state |1⟩:\n", 
      "Matrix([[0], [0], [0], [sqrt(3)]])\n" 
     ] 
    } 
   ], 
   "source": [ 
    "from sympy.physics.quantum import represent\n", 
    "from sympy.physics.quantum.qubit import Qubit\n", 
    "from sympy import sqrt, Matrix\n", 
    "\n", 
    "# Define the entangled state |ψ⟩\n", 
    "psi = (Qubit('00') + Qubit('10') - Qubit('11')) / sqrt(3)\n", 
    "\n", 
    "# Write the state as a column vector\n", 
    "state_vector = represent(psi)\n", 
    "\n", 
    "# Calculate the probability of measuring the first qubit in the state |1⟩\n", 
    "# The probability is given by the sum of the absolute squares of the amplitudes of |10⟩ and |11⟩.\n", 
    "prob_1st_qubit_1 = abs(state_vector[2])**2 + abs(state_vector[3])**2\n", 
    "\n", 
    "# Calculate the state of the system if we measure the first qubit to be in the state |1⟩\n", 
    "# The resulting state will be the normalization of the |11⟩ component of the state vector\n", 
    "# Since |10⟩ does not contribute (it is not present in the entangled state), we only consider |11⟩\n", 
    "resulting_state_vector = represent(Qubit('11')) * sqrt(3)\n", 
    "\n", 
    "# Print the results\n", 
    "print(\"State as a column vector:\")\n", 
    "print(Matrix(state_vector))\n", 
    "\n", 
    "print(\"\\nProbability of the first qubit being in state |1⟩:\")\n", 
    "print(prob_1st_qubit_1.evalf())\n", 
    "\n", 
    "print(\"\\nState of the system after measuring the first qubit in state |1⟩:\")\n", 
    "print(Matrix(resulting_state_vector))" 
   ],
